==Old English==
===Etymology===
Germanic ''*watar'', from Indo-European ''*u̯odr̥''.

''Germanic cognates:'' Old Frisian [[weter]], Old Saxon [[watar]] (Dutch [[water#Dutch|water]]), Old High German [[wazzar]] (German [[Wasser]]), Old Norse [[vatn]] (Swedish [[vatten]]), Gothic [[𐍅𐌰𐍄𐍉]].

''Indo-European cognates:'' Hittite ''watar'', Sanskrit [[उन्द्]], Greek [[ὕδωρ]], Old Church Slavonic [[вода]] (Polish [[woda]]), Lithuanian [[vanduo|vanduõ]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'wæteɹ/

===Noun===
